name: 싱
contents: 정말. 의심할 때 행여나 될까 하고 추측하는 뜻을 나타내는 말

name: 에게
contents: 이끼. 생각하는 바와 달랐을 때 이거 머냐는 뜻을 나타내는 말

name: 게메
contents: 게메서란=게메선. 그러기에. 과연 그렇다는 뜻을 나타내는 말

name: 게¹
contents: 겐. 그래. 해라 할 자리에 그렇다는 뜻을 나타내는 말

name: 다슴
contents: 다심. 어붓. 의리로 맺어진 인륜 관계

name: 히뜨거니
contents: 히뜩. 새벽 하늘이 부옇게 밝아가는 꼴

name: 펜두룽이
contents: 펜주룽이=펜드렁이<핀두룽이. 시치미 떼고 그대로 있는 꼴, 겁내지 않고 태연한 꼴.

name: 어잉간이
engContents: One way or other, not bad

name: 소드락이
contents: 수두락이. 작은 것을 한 곳에 많이

name: 복삭
contents: <박삭<북삭. 털이나 풀 따위가 많이 돋은 꼴

name: 바락
contents: 바락이. 갑자기 성내는 꼴. 한번에 많이 힘차게 넣거나 얻어 들이는 꼴

name: 멜락
contents: 멜싹<몰락=물싹<밀락=밀싹. 조심성 없이 디디는 꼴, 힘없이 주저앉는 꼴

name: 우싹다
engContents: It feels like being pricked with a needle

name: 옹색다
contents: 돈이 없어 곤란하다, 거래가 막히다, 자리가 좁다.
engContents: Suffer from financial difficulties, business relations got broken off, space is narrow

name: 오슬오슬다
contents: 시루떡 따위가 부스러지지 않고 옹골차다, 잔 것이 싱싱하다.

name: 어중간다
contents: 어중구랑다. ① 몽종하다, 의심스럽다. ② 흐리멍덩하다.

name: 르르다
contents: 르륵다. ① 목이 시원하다. ② 마음이 가라앉는 느낌이 있다.

name: 싯다
contents: 잇다. 있다, 계시다(싯다, 싯고, 싯지, 시어, 시니).

name: 싸다
contents: ① 그만한 가치가 있다. ② 그래도 마땅하다(죽어도 싸다).

name: 살치다
engContents: Get fat,  a straw rope is thick

name: 사락사락다
contents: ① 깔깔하다. ② 물기가 없어 포근하다.
engContents: It feels coarse, cozy without dampness

name: 반조롱다
contents: 반주롱다. 단정하다. 깨끗하다. 아무 것도 없다.

name: 지직다
contents: 피륙 짜입새나 새끼 꼬임새가 여무지다, 마음이 굳세다.

name: 미식다
engContents: Someting is found common, piled up

name: 다
engContents: Dark, the outlook for the future is discouraging

name: 흘트다
engContents: Some thick liquid flows, water drops

name: 훌트다²
contents: ① 문질러 미끄럽게 하다. ② 액체를 걸레로 훔치다.
engContents: Rub to make smooth, wipe water with cloth

name: 퍼붓다
contents: ① 비가 쏟아지다. ② 말을 쏟아내다.
engContents: The rain pours down, speak out

name: 아지다
contents: ① 한 쪽이 이지러지다. ② 성질이 원만하지 못하다.

name: 트다 ²
engContents: Have a corn on the sole of one's foot

name: 어르다
contents: 얼르다. ① 얼씬거리다. ② 일하는 곳을 돌아다니다. ③ 남녀가 서로 관계하다.
engContents: Keep coming around, wander about work places, make love

name: 벨르다
engContents: Open out to see the inside

name: 벨라지다
engContents: It opens and shows the inside

name: 데우다
contents: 식은 것을 슬쩍 삶아 뜨겁게 하다.
engContents: Warm up again food that got cold

name: 다끄(닦으)다
contents: = 따끄(딲으)다 ① 딲다. ② 탁주를 끊여 소주를 만들다.

name: 다
contents: ① 갈다(磨). ② 바꾸다, 갈다(替).

name: 기다
contents: ① 갈기다. ② 오줌을 힘차게 싸다.

name: 딱다
engContents: Move something or one's body a bit

name: 득다
engContents: Loaded with stuff in the shed

name: 오매기
engContents: Rice cake to be an ingredient of alcohol

name: 약괴
engContents: Yakgwa, Korean cookie having a square shape

name: 식게
engContents: Korean sweet drink made with fermented rice

name: 쉰다리
engContents: Korean sweet drink made with fermented rice

name: 술오매기
contents: 오매기. 술을 빚기 위하여 만드는 떡인데 둥글고 가운데에 구멍이 있는 조떡
engContents: Rice cake to be an ingredient of alcohol, which has a round shape with a hole in the center

name: 셍밥
engContents: Rice which is not cooked enough

name: 래기
engContents: Person whose body in part has become twisted

name: 큰아방
engContents: The eldest uncle in father side

name: 큰삼춘
engContents: The eldest uncle in father side

name: 촐래기
engContents: One who wanders around and acts on impulse

name: 촐람생이
contents: 초라니. 행동이 빠르고 기괴한 사람의 별칭
engContents: Exorcist who appears in woman's dress at a court rite

name: 초라니
contents: 촐람생이. 행동이 빠르고 기괴한 사람의 별칭
engContents: Someone who is nimble and excentric

name: 유지남-우영
engContents: a field used to have citron trees

name: 엉덕-물
engContents: water kept in a rock cave

name: 숯굿
engContents: a puddle dug at the spot to make charcoals

name: 쇠선-밧
contents: 밭이 넓고 골이 길어 밭갈때 소가 휴식을 위해 섰던 밭
engContents: a spot where cows made a stop for a rest while plowing as the field was very large and long

name: 병두-왓
engContents: a drill field for soldiers in old days

name: 반-못
engContents: this name was derived from the origin the filed wouldn’t get dry even in drought

name: 돗-바령
contents: 멧돼지가 많이 몰려와서 짓밟았다하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact lots of wild pigs rushed in and trempled down the place

name: 곰숫-터
contents: 토굴과 같이 큰 가마를 만들어 숯을 구웠던 곳
engContents: this used to be a spot where they make charcoals in a big pit

name: 아낭-거리
engContents: a street having lots of Awae trees

name: 개남-술
engContents: a village having lots of Gae trees

name: 고장남-밧
engContents: it suggests there used to be lots of flower plants

name: 섬-팟
engContents: a remote field like an island

name: 빌레-통
contents: 바위틈에 물이 고이는 통이 있는 곳
engContents: a crack in rocks, where water gathers

name: 서근-빌레
engContents: this beach has lots of rocks having a look of dragon head

name: 쥐영-밧
engContents: it suggests there were lots of holes where mice lived in

name: 살쏜디-왓
engContents: this name suggests target boards used to be set up in this field for archery practice

name: 골-왓
engContents: this name suggests there used to be a cave in this field

name: 노-적눌
engContents: this place is where a pile of pebbles is located like a stack of grain

name: 지왓-골
engContents: a field having lots of roofing tiles around

name: 관가름
contents: 주초석과 기왓장, 자기 파편들이 많이 널려있는 곳
engContents: this was where foundations stones, roofing tiles and broken porcelain pieces are often found

name: 생이집-목
engContents: a spot where a hut to keep bier and accessories was located

name: 곱은 여
contents: 수면에 보일 듯 말듯 한 암초

name: 게와당
engContents: a yard looking like a pocket

name: 산물깍
engContents: a stream by which springwater flows out

name: 구린질 목
contents: 속이 텅 빈, 웅덩이가 있는  길목
engContents: a corner where there is an empty puddle

name: 고동여
engContents: a reef where turban shells can get catched a lot

name: 왕모살냇기
engContents: a beach which was constituted by big sands

name: 갱이여
engContents: a reef having a look of a crab

name: 개압코지
engContents: this name suggests it is located in front of the port

name: 안캣머리
contents: 비교적 포구 안에 자리잡고 있다고 해서 유래
engContents: this name suggests it is located inside the port

name: 화성개
contents: 삼신인이 꽃상자를 발견하고, 그 떠오른 곳
engContents: a port where the three spirits found a flower box

name: 터우개
engContents: a spot where they used to anchor rafts

name: 황노알
contents: 삼선녀가 상륙하던 무렵의 황금빛 노을을 뜻하는 지명
engContents: it means the golden sunset when the three fairies came down

engContents: this place was where the three fairies came down with grain seeds, a calf and a foal

name: 먹벵디
contents: 주변에 못이 있었고 지역이 넓은데서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there was a pond in the neighborhood and the area was spacy

name: 마풀림동산
contents: 본향제인 마풀림제를 지낼 때, 신의 의복을 내걸어 말렸다는 터
engContents: this was a spot where a gods costume used to be hung to dry during a sharminst service for the village

name: 당동산
engContents: this name was derived from the hill having a shrine

name: 상둣동산
engContents: this used to be a place where villagers gather and have a meeting

name: 물곰밧동산
engContents: a hill having a field which is easily sunk under water

name: 두러물동산
engContents: a hill which is not well drained when raining

name: 금붕애동산
engContents: a hill looks like a goldfish

name: 촘생이-케
contents: 촘생은 목초, 목초가 많았던 넓은 지역
engContents: this name suggests this place was abundant in grass for pasturage

name: 찍-여
contents: 평평한 곳에 오뚝하게 박혀있는 모양을 한 여
engContents: this name suggests a rock stuck into the flat ground, standing upright

name: 너른-걸
contents: 걸은 돌멩이나 바닥돌로 이루어진 바다 밭을 의미하는 바다지명의 접미사이다. 그 지역이 넓어서 붙여진 이름
engContents: Geol implies stone or sea bed, and this name means a large geol

name: 베락-마진-소
engContents: this name was derived from the origin that there was a thunderbolt striking near a cow

name: 큰-속동-개-코지
contents: 큰 파도가 코지로 치면 속돌이 많이 올라온다.
engContents: lots of stones in the water are revealed when a big wave hits the cape

name: 마풀림
engContents: this name suggests a grassy place

name: 보재기-다루
engContents: this name suggests a small field owned by a fisher

name: 머생이-왓
contents: 머생이는 빌레가 계속 연결된 상태, 그런 형태의 밭
engContents: Meosaengyi is broad and flat rocks linked to each other and this name means a field of such feature

name: 징줄-논
contents: 징줄은 수초를 뜻함, 이 지역에 징줄이 자생하여 불려진 이름
engContents: Jingjul is a water plant and it spontaenously grows in this area

name: 꼼장이
engContents: it means a Gomangnon which is not easily seen

name: 빌륵-밧
engContents: this name came from its dampness

name: 고냉이-머들-아즌-밧
contents: 밭 가운데 고인돌처럼 큰 돌이 앉아 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a large rock like a dolmen(Goindol) standing in the middle of the field

name: 도채비-골
contents: 가축의 뼈 등이 습도가 높은 날 밤에 인광이 나타나므로 도깨비가 나타나는 지역으로 불림
engContents: this name was derived from the origin that they thought phosphorescence from animals as monster(Doggaebi)

name: 불미-왓
engContents: this name was derived from its bellows-shaped feature

name: 혼착-밧
contents: 한쪽 밭을 말함, 넓은 밭을 분할하여 자녀에게나누어 준 밭
engContents: it means part of a large field which was divided and shared by ones children

name: 구럼비
contents: 구엄->구엄부->구럼비로 변형되어 불림, 옛날 해안가를 중심으로 초가로 된 9개의 작은 암자들이 있어 구럼비/구암비라 불림
engContents: this name came from the origin that 9 small buddhist temples with a straw-thatched roof along the beach. the word, Gureombi originates through Gueop from Gueopbu

name: 꿩-망-동산
contents: 꿩몰이 사냥을 할 때 꿩의 위치를 살피는 동산
engContents: while hunting pheasants, they detected pheasants on this hill

name: 매-아진-돌
engContents: a rock used to be sit on by hawks

name: 여이-물
engContents: a fountain by which foxes showed up

name: 섯-언-새미
engContents: a cold well in the west

name: 동-언-새미
engContents: a cold well in the east

name: 굿-밧-거리
contents: 지난 날 굿을 많이하여 불려지는 이름
engContents: this name came from the origin that they often performed sharmanist services in the past

name: 거믄-머들
engContents: this name suggests a pile of dark stones

name: 노린-빌레
engContents: this name suggests the base rock has a redish yellow color

name: 돌-혹
contents: 돌절구 같은 데서 샘이나와 붙여진 명칭
engContents: this name has an origin that water sprang up from a stone mortar

name: 쇠-에움-밧
contents: 자신의 밭에 소를 가두어 방목하던 곳
engContents: this spot was used as a ranch for raising cows in ones field

name: 마장-밧
contents: 자신의 밭에 마를 가두어 방목하던 곳
engContents: this spot was used as a ranch for raising horses in ones field

name: 행기-소
contents: 기우제 지낼 때 제관들이 목욕하여 기우제 지내는 장소
engContents: this is a place where officiating sharmanist performed a ritual service praying for rain by taking a bath

name: 합순-밧
contents: 합순은 풀이 있는 밭, 어려운 시절 합순을 식용으로 범벅을 만들어 먹음
engContents: Hamsun is a kind of grass which used to be eaten when people didnt have enough food

name: 거무리-왓
engContents: this name was derived from the origin that a bride from Sagye came to live here

name: 번제-드르
contents: 동네사람들이 추렴하여 나누어주는 곳이라하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the origin that villagers used to collect things to share here

name: 식-궤
engContents: Sik means a cat, and this name suggests a cabin where a cat used to live in

name: 졸레-왓
engContents: this name means that this field was sold in exchange for empty heads of grain

name: 벨진-마루
engContents: a special camp was set up to defend on this hlll

name: 쇠-저리는-자리
contents: 소를 배로 운반할 때 소를 묶고 풀었던 자리를 말한다
engContents: this place used to be a spot where they tie and untie cows while displacing them

name: 콧-쿰
contents: 구멍이 마치 콧구멍처럼 두개 뚫려 있는 지형
engContents: this place features two large holes like nostrils

name: 벵풍-석
contents: 절벽이 병풍을 펼쳐 놓은 것처럼 주상절리가 발달된 지형
engContents: this place features well-developped pillar-shaped joint, whose cliff looks like a unfolded screen

name: 두머니-물
contents: 두는 머리를 의미, 예로부터 아기엄마들이 젖이 잘 나오지 않을 때 이곳에 와서 두머니물을 먹고 목욕하면 젖이 잘 나온다는 데서 붙여진 이름
engContents: Du means head, and this name was derived from the origin that mothers of infants came here, drank the water and bathed in it for better pumping of their breast milk

name: 물깍-먼-여
engContents: this means a remote rock from the beach

name: 공물깍-먼-여
engContents: this means a remote rock from Gongmulggak

name: 정포제-동산
engContents: this name suggests people performed a Poje(a religious service for the village) on this hill

name: 둠부-소
engContents: this name suggests the pond has lots of sea weed called Deumbuk coming from the sea

name: 겡이-돌레
contents: 바다에 사는 게 모양의 작은 밭
engContents: this name suggests the field has a look of a crab

name: 빈네-코지
contents: 그 모양이 여자머리에 꽂는 비녀를 닮았다고 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its looks of Binyeo, a Korean hairpin for woman

name: 진-모루
engContents: this name was derived from the fact soldiers used to pitch a camp during Japanese invasion of Korea in 1592

name: 당-팟
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be a shrine

name: 무남-통
engContents: this name came from mulnamneun-tong implying abundancy in water

name: 고막-곶
engContents: this name suggests that it used to be a place where people put up a shanty to live in

name: 샛-도
engContents: it means an entrance between two things

name: 송남-모루
contents: 마루모양이 학이 날개를 벌려 새끼를 품을 형세라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of the ridge reflecting a crane spreading the wings to embrace its chickens

name: 한-무덤-골
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there were lots of tombs

name: 수루막-동산
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of camps placed in a row

name: 외진-모루
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of soldiers pitching a camp

name: 기진-모루
contents: 장군 깃발이 휘날리는 모습을 한 형상의 동산
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a generals flag flapping in the wind

name: 애기난-갯도
contents: 냇가 입구에서 애기를 낳았다 하여 불려짐
engContents: this name suggests there was a baby delivery at this entrace of the stream

name: 구진내-도
contents: 구진은 불편함을 말한다. 하천 건너다니기 불편해서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was difficult to cross the stream as Gujin means difficulty

name: 닥-돌레
engContents: this name suggests dak trees(paper mulberry) used to be raised in this field

name: 도고리-왓
contents: 도고리는 소나 돼지의 여물통으로 도고리를 만들어주고 얻은 밭
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this field was given in exchange of making a dogori(a manger) as a gift

name: 쳇대-왓
contents: 촛대를 하나 만들어 주고받은 밭이라 하여 불려짐
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this field was given in exchange of making a candlestick

name: 가문-다리
contents: 가문는 가늘다의 뜻으로 외나무다리가 있었던 곳
engContents: this name including a word Gamun meaning thin was derived from the fact there used to be a single-log bridge

name: 제-돌레
engContents: it means this field used to have a  tree called Je tree

name: 소근-밧
contents: 소근은 고생하다는 뜻으로 그만큼 힘들었던 밭
engContents: Sogeun means trouble and this name suggests there were lots of works in the field

name: 세밋-도
contents: 샘이 있는 곳으로 가는 길 입구
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is the entrance to the well

name: 매남-빌레
engContents: this name was derived from the base rock having lots of Japanese apricot trees

name: 건저귀-왓
contents: 허물을 고쳐주는 귀신이 살고 있는 밭
engContents: it was believed that a ghost correcting faults used to live in this field

name: 검붕낭앝-밧
engContents: this field used to have Punggae trees around

name: 제민당
contents: 조문하던 곳, 사람이 죽으면 토롱해 두었던 밭들이 있던 곳
engContents: this is used to be a field to simply bury the dead

name: 걱대-왓
engContents: this name refers to a field where religious wooden sculptures were posted

name: 물마근-밧
engContents: it refers to a field stopping the water flow

name: 모-팡
contents: 작은 분지형태로 높이 1m, 남북 길이 2m, 동서 길이 1m 정도의 바위가 솟아있는 형국에서 불려짐
engContents: a kind of small  basin. Iwhich has a rock that is 1 meter high, 2 meter-long between north and south, 1 meter-long between east and west

name: 굴메-소
engContents: it means a pond over which a shadow was casted

name: 구명-물
contents: 굴명물이 와전, 여름철에 천둥번개가 치면서 땅이 울려야 솟아나는 샘을 구명물이라한다
engContents: this name came from Gulmyeongmul which is a fountain springing up from the ground hit by lightning in summer season

name: 마근-물
contents: 저수지 물이 합류되는 지점, 마근는 막다를 뜻함
engContents: it means a spot where water in the reserves joins. mageun means prevent

name: 폴두-곱지
contents: 하천변의 도로형태가 팔이 굽은 모양이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the road along the stream has a look of a bended arm

name: 안 게
contents: 게의 집게발 모양을 하고 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name came from the looks of crab claw

name: 셋도리-통
contents: 두 번째 위치에 있다고 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: it means that took the second place

name: 무근-가름
contents: 설촌 되기 전 동네라하여 불려진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the community was existing even before forming a village

name: 존-내-틈
contents: 작은 내 사이란 뜻으로 불려진 이름
engContents: this refers to a space between small streams

name: 제낭-코지
engContents: this name suggests there are Norinjae trees

name: 움통-밧
contents: 지형이 움푹 들어가 있어 불려진 이름
engContents: it suggests the ground is sunken

name: 살체기-도
contents: 살을 이용하여 엉기성기 만든문을 입구에 설치 한 것으로 머체동산위에 설치하여 불려진 이름
engContents: this gate roughly made with wooden frames was installed over meoche hill

name: 무주-왓
contents: 주인이 없는 넓은 초원에서 우마들을 훈련시킨데서 불려진 이름
engContents: this name suggests cows and horses were trained in this deserted wide field

name: 볼레-골
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there are lots of borisu(bo tree)

name: 웃뒷빌레-못
contents: 못을 파서 우마에게 물을 먹이던 못
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this pond used to provide cows and horses with water

name: 알섯-네커리
contents: 마을 서쪽에 있는 사거리라하여 불려진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this is a crossroad in the west of the village

name: 머레기-동산
engContents: it means a hill with lots of wild grapes

name: 종낭-굴
engContents: it suggests the cave used to have lots of Ddaejuk trees around

name: 모시-모루
engContents: it means a hill producing lots of ramies

name: 주막-동산
contents: 옛날 이곳에 술을 팔았던 주막이 있었던 자리
engContents: this name suggests there used to be a tavern in old days

name: 올래-동산
engContents: it means a hill in front of the house

name: 골머체
contents: 곤머체고운 동산을 나타냄, 골머체로 와전되어 불림
engContents: this name was derived from Gonmeoche(beautiful hill)

name: 몰진-밧
contents: 말을 진상하기 위해 말을 모아 두었던 밭
engContents: this field used to be a place to collect horses before presenting them to the king

name: 개우지-코지
contents: 바닷가 쪽을 향해 쭉 뻗어 나가서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it got outstretched towards the sea

name: 성제-돌
engContents: this name suggests two rocks stand together like brothers

name: 테우리-통
contents: 소 먹이는 테우리가 망을 보던 곳
engContents: this place is where a taewoori(a herdboy) used to stand guard

name: 생이-돌
engContents: this means migratory birds have a rest on this stone

name: 누릉낭-동산
engContents: this means a hill of elm trees

name: 독-통
engContents: this name suggests a look of a hen sitting on eggs

name: 섬들이-왓
engContents: this name suggests this is a palce where islands are not visible

name: 한지내-콤
contents: 내가 넓은 모양. 한지는 넓다 이고 콤은 일정지역을 나타냄
engContents: this name consists of Hanji(wide) and Kom(a certain place)

name: 맹-살
contents: 비가 많이 와서 범람하면 물로 채워지는 곳
engContents: this place used to be filled with water when flooding

name: 쇠소-깍
contents: 하효마을의 본래 명칭은 쇠둔이다. 효돈천하구에 있는 소라 하여 쇠소라불려지고 있으며, 쇠소의 마지막이라하여 붙여진 이름 깍은 맨마지막을 나타냄
engContents: the original name of Hahyo village is Soedun. this word consists of Soeso meaning a swamp at the end of Hyodoncheon(Hyodon stream) and Kkak meaning the last

name: 소금-막
contents: 막은 막사를 의미, 소금을 구웠던 곳
engContents: this place used to be a spot for burning salt

name: 소나물-곳
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the depth of the place is quite long

name: 재-통
contents: 모몰짚을 태워 재를 만들었던 곳, 모몰은 메밀
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be a place to get ash(Jae) from burning straws

name: 도-틀-왓
engContents: this name suggests that it is a field open to the road

name: 돌박남-밧
engContents: this name suggests the place used to be a field full of camellias(Dongbaeknamu)

name: 닥-돌래
contents: 닥은 닥나무, 돌레는 둥그렇게 생긴 작은 밭이다. 닥나무를 재배했던 곳
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be the place to cultivate Dak trees(paper mulberry)

name: 고막-곶
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was used to be a forest

name: 믠-돌
contents: 믠은 믠짝으로 아무것도 없음을 말함. 즉 주위에 아무것도 없이 돌만 있는 곳
engContents: this name was derived from the word, Myeun meaning there is nothing but stones

name: 써금-바령
contents: 소, 말 등을 밤에 풀어두었던 곳
engContents: this place used to be a spot for releasing cows and horses at night

name: 큰-가름
contents: 마을 안에 또하나의 큰마을을 이룬 것
engContents: it means a large village in another village

name: 구덕찬-돌
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of stone with holes

name: 애기업게-돌
engContents: this name came from the stone having a look of one carrying a baby on the back

name: 왜-통
engContents: it used to be a place to manufacture tiles

name: 노용-동산
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a roe

name: 말축-밧
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a horse leg

name: 천아오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is an oak tree

name: 정물오름
engContents: this name was derived from a fountain name,  Jeongmul,

name: 새미소오름
contents: 깊은 샘이 있는 오름이라 붙여진 이름
engContents: it means a hill with a deep well

name: 느지리오름
engContents: this name was derived from Neujiri, the former name of Sangmyeongri

name: 갯거리오름
contents: 두 마리의 개가 꼬리를 끌고 누운 형상에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of two dogs lying down with their tails outstreched

name: 마오름
contents: 산이 말 형체를 하고 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a horse

name: 송아오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a calf

name: 노꼬물오름
contents: 노꼬물 전설에서 유래한 샘이 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the well known in the Nokomul legend

name: 염통오름
contents: 사람 가슴 안의 심장 형국이라 하여 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a human heart

name: 가세오름
contents: 산봉오리가 두 갈래로 갈라진것이 가위(가세)와 같아 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of the mountain top divided into two like scissors

name: 벵곳오름
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from the fact there were byeongkotpul(ground ivy)

name: 번널오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a board

name: 백약이오름
engContents: this suggests there are one hundred kinds of herbs growing

name: 산굼부리
engContents: this word consists of a hole(Gum) and a mountaintop(Buri)

name: 부대오름
contents: 화전, 개간지의 뜻인 부대기의 줄인말인듯 하나 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was possibly derived from the word, Budaegi meaning the ground burned off for cultivation or developed land

name: 바농오름
engContents: this name came from the forest full of thornbush

name: 돔베오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill looks as even as a chopping board

name: 구그네오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance of a Gugeune(rake)

name: 궤펭이오름
engContents: this name suggests that there is a rock cave(Goe)

name: 까끄레기
contents: 마소를 방목한다는 말인 고끄레 간다는데서 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the words, Goggre ganda meaning farming cows and horses

name: 흙붉은오름
contents: 붉은 흙의 산등이 멀리서 보일만큼 드러나 있어서 연유
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the ridge covered with red earth is seen from a distance

name: 족은드레오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill is standing in the small field(Jokeundeure)

name: 큰드레오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill is standing in the large field(Keudeure)

name: 베리오름
contents: 오름의 바닷가쪽에 벼랑(베리)이 있다 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a cliff(Byeorang) to the direction of the sea from this hill

name: 베두리오름
contents: 오름머리 남쪽에 별무리처럼 바위가 모여있다 하여 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact many rocks gather south of the top like a group of stars

name: 불칸디오름
engContents: this name means a burnt hill(Bulkandi)

name: 쌀손장오리
engContents: this name was derived from the legend three spirits shot arrows from this hill

name: 태역장오리
engContents: this name suggests there used to be a large lawn

name: 도들오름
engContents: it means the way it rises looks beautiful

name: 노리오름
engContents: this name suggests there used to be lots of roes

name: 노리손이
contents: 노리는 노루를, 손은 쏘다의 옛말로 노루가 많아 노루사냥으로 이름났던 데서 연유
engContents: this name is combination of a word, Nori(roe) and another word, Soni(shoot), which means it is popular for roe hunting

name: 광이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the features of a cat

name: 남짓은오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks overgrown with trees

name: 골머리오름
engContents: this name suggests this is the first top of ninty nine hill tops

name: 걸시오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a latch

name: 거친오름
contents: 몸집이 크고 산세가 험한데다 숲이 어수선히 우거져 거칠게 보여 연유함
engContents: this name suggests this big mountain has steep and bumpy features and the forest is overgrown with trees

name: 솔오름
contents: 쌀을 쌓아올린 형태, 살(피부)처럼 매끈하다 하여 유래했다는 등의 의견이 있음
engContents: this name is interpreted in many ways; the looks of a stack of rice or as smooth as human skin and etc.

name: 시오름
engContents: this name was derived from Suoreum(Male-oreum)

name: 베린내오름
contents: 벼랑(베리)을 이루는 천제연 근처에 있어 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is located near to Cheonjeyeon forming a cliff(Byoerang)

name: 방애오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of Banga(mill)

name: 더데오름
contents: 더더(加加)에서 온 것으로 산이 중첩돼 있음을 뜻함
engContents: this name suggests the looks of mountain upon mountain

name: 넉시오름
contents: 넋 나간 소가 누워있는 형국에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of an absent-minded cow lying down

name: 걸세오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a latch

name: 이승이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a wildcat

name: 체오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a winnow(che)

name: 윤드리오름
contents: 넓은 들에 누워있는 오름이라 하나 어원이 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from an orem(hill) lying down on a large field, which hasnt been ascertained

name: 식은이오름
contents: 산맥이 벌써 식었다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name means the mountains have got cold

name: 밭돌오름
contents: 돌이 많은 오름이나 안돌오름과 구별하기 위해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was given to this stony hill in order to distinguish from Andoloreum

name: 안돌오름
contents: 돌이 많은 오름이나 밭돌오름과 구별하기 위해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was given to this stony hill in order to distinguish from Baldoloreum

name: 아진오름
contents: 두 다리를 벌리고 앉아있는 모양에서 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the looks one is sitting down with two legs outstretched

name: 아부오름
engContents: this used to be once called Aporeum  but later changed into Abuoreum

name: 손지오름
contents: 작지만 한라산과 비슷하게 생겨 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it takes after Mountain Halla as if a grandson(Sonja) of it

name: 비치미
contents: 꿩이 나는 형국이라 하여 붙여졌다 하나 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from the appearance like a flying pheasant

name: 북오름
engContents: this name was derived from the look of a drum

name: 민오름
engContents: this name was derived from the smooth appearance

name: 당오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be a shrine

name: 다랑쉬
contents: 산봉우리 분화구가 달처럼 둥글게 보인다 하여 붙여짐
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of the crater like the moon

name: 거친오름
contents: 크고 거칠어보인다, 거쳐가는 오름이다, 거린오름의 와전이다 등의 유래가 있음
engContents: it has many interpretations such as big and rough, a transit hill, a name derived from Georin hill and etc.

name: 거슨새미오름
contents: 물이 한라산쪽으로 흘러나온다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water flows towards Mountain Halla

name: 거미오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance its ridges are spreading in all directions like a spider web

name: 쇠머리오름
contents: 우도의 형상이 소의 형상이고 그 머리부위에 해당하여 유래함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it looks like a head of cow

name: 이달오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there are two mountains(Dal)

name: 사제비오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact sparrow hawks are living here

name: 빈네오름
contents: 봉우리 쪽에 쪽진 머리에 비녀를 꽂은 모습을 한 바위가 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a rock looking like a lady with a hair pin(Binyeo) on the top

name: 물메오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a pond on the top

name: 노로오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there are lots of roes(Noro)

name: 폭낭오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be a big hackberry(Poknang)

name: 하늬복이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is locatd where the north wind(Hanibaram) frequently blows

name: 마복이오름
contents: 남풍(마파람)이 많이 부는 곳에 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is locatd where the south wind(Maparam) frequently blows

name: 바굼지오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance having a look of bat

name: 도너리오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has a large entrance

name: 넙게오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance having a look of a large crab

name: 골른오름
contents: 쌍둥이(골오기)에서 유래하여 두오름이 나란히 있다 하여 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the word Gologi(twins), whose twin hills are standing side by side.

name: 굴메오름
engContents: it means this mountain happened to generate as an additional outcome

name: 거린오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance that the hill is divided into two

name: 족은물뫼
engContents: people call this small hill this way to distinguish from Keunmulmoe(big hill)

name: 큰물뫼
contents: 원래 물뫼(물미)라 했던것이 동쪽의 족은물뫼와 구별하여 큰쿨뫼라 하게 됨
engContents: this used to be called Mulmoe once but later called Keunmulmoe as distinguishment fromJokeunmulmoe in the east

name: 족은왕뫼
contents: 왕뫼 가까이에 있는 작은 오름이라는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this small hill is standing near to Wangmoe

name: 왕뫼
engContents: this hill name was derived from its look of prince

name: 유건에오름
contents: 유생이 쓰는 유건의 모양처럼 생겼다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its look of Korean traditional student hat

name: 본지오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be lots of the oriental bittersweets

name: 바우오름
contents: 바위가 많이 드러난 봉우리에서 바위가 바우로 변형되 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its top with lots of rocks

name: 젯그린동산
contents: 어미의 젖을 그리는 어린 개의 형국에서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its look of a puppy missing its mother dogs milk

name: 뒤굽은이
contents: 남동쪽을 산머리로 하여 북쪽으로 등성마루가 구부러져 있다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has its head in the south east and the ridge in the north

name: 통오름
contents: 물통, 밥통 등의 통처럼 생겼다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name reflects it looks like a container such as a water bottle or a rice bowl

name: 돌미
contents: 동쪽 산머리에 큰 바위무더기가 박힌 돌산이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this stony mountain has a huge file of rocks in the east head

name: 낭끼오름
contents: 나무들이 서 있는 변두리라는 뜻에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was a countryside having trees around

name: 통바금물
contents: 냇물이 고이는 곳이 우물(통)처럼 생겨서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the place to form a puddle looks like a well

name: 행기소물
contents: 샘의 모양이 밥사발 같고 물이 맑고 항상 고여있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has a look of rice bowl and constantly running clear water

name: 등창물
contents: 맑은 샘이 아무리 가물어도 바닥을 드러내지 않는다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this cear water never runs dry

name: 당두둑물
contents: 설문대할망당이 있는 두둑이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this ridge name was named after Seolmunhalmangdang

name: 겐놉샘물
contents: 물통처럼 둥그렇게 생기고 갯이끼가 껴있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: 물통처럼 둥그렇게 생기고 갯이끼가 껴있어 붙여진 이름

name: 새기미산물
contents: 차고 맑은 샘이 연중 마르지 않고 흐른다 해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact cold and clear water springs up all the year round

name: 고씨땅물
contents: 고씨성을 가진 사람 땅 부근에 샘이 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was located near Mr.Gos property

name: 고능개물
contents: 바닷가 소하천의 앞 바다가 가느다랗다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: the name was derived from the fact the front sea looks thin

name: 산열이통물
contents: 더위를 식히고 땀띠를 없애기 위해 이용하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water was used to release the heat and cure the heat rashes

name: 노단새미
contents: 노단은 오른쪽을 일컫는 제주지역어로,  한라산을 향해 거슬러 흐르지 않는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: Nodan means a right direction in Jeju dialect and this name was derived from the fact it does not flow  in the direction of Halla Mountain

name: 거슨새미
contents: 한라산쪽으로 거슬러 흐르는 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it flows upward in the direction of Halla Mountain

name: 옥빰물
contents: 올빼미가 밤마다 운다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact owls sing every night

name: 괴물
contents: 궤에서 나오는 물이라 하여 궤물, 괴물이라 함
engContents: this name was derived from Goe

name: 통물
engContents: this name was derived from the village called Tongcheonri

name: 양재소물
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be Yangjaeso

name: 이당장물
contents: 당장 직함을 가진 이씨가 팠다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the well was dug by Mr.Lee having a title of Dangjang

name: 감수물
engContents: this name was derived from its sweetness

name: 양가수
contents: 양씨가 판 샘물이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the fountain was dug by Mr. Yang

name: 넘나물
contents: 비가 오면 물이 넘친다 하여 지어진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water got overflown when it rained

name: 알정물
engContents: this name means a well on the downside

name: 웃정물
contents: 우마가 들어가지 못하게 정을 놓은데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact they posted a bar to keep cows and horses away

name: 곤물
contents: 고은물로 부르다가 곤물이 되었다는 설과 곶물이 곤물이 되었다는 설이 있다
engContents: according to two interpretations, one is the name came from Goeunmul and the other is it came from Gotmul

name: 산통물
contents: 넘치는법 없이 늘 그만큼 채워져 있어 살아있는 물이라 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water is always filled up as same as if it is alive

name: 가르메물
contents: 사람 머리꼭대기 정수리처럼 생겼다 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance of the top looking like a human head

name: 부개높물
contents: 물고기들이 펄쩍펄쩍 뛰는게 보인다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it can have a view of fish jumping out of the water

name: 몰성괴물
contents: 수산평의 말과 소를 이 포구에서 선적하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact horses and cows from Susanpyeong used to be shipped at this port

name: 며느리다리물
contents: 한 집 며느리가 밤에 당을 찾아가다 빠져 죽은 후로 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the legend a housewife happened to be drown in this water while going to the shrine at night

name: 색통물
contents: 소들이 즐겨 물을 먹었던 곳에서 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact cows used to drink this water

name: 앞펄
contents: 앞쪽에 있는 펄 이름을 따서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this was named after the tideland ahead

name: 주군디물
contents: 군대가 주둔할 당시 그들이 이용한 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact soldiers used to drink this water while thier stationing

name: 수전
contents: 조선 초기에 수전소가 있던곳이라 하여 유래된 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its origin as the navy camp in Chosun Kingdom

name: 당두포
contents: 오조리 당의 머리쪽에 있는 포구라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the port was located at the head of Ojoridang(shrine)

name: 큰개물
contents: 마을의 중심이 되는 큰 포구가 있는 곳에 있어 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its location in the large port as the center of the village

name: 테우리동산물
contents: 근처의 동산에서 백중제를 지낸데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact they performed a religious service for a good harvest

name: 배탕개물
contents: 근처에 배탕개란 지명이 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the place name, Baetanggae in the neighborhood

name: 진모살물
contents: 포구 근처에 모래밭이 길게 펼쳐져 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a long sand bed near the port

name: 코지산물
contents: 근처에 사람 코의 형상의 바위가 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the rock having a look of human nose nearby

name: 앞개물
contents: 마을 앞에 자리잡았다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the location in front of the village

name: 만물
contents: 근처 바닷가 일대가 조그마한 만을 형성하고 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the seashore forms a small gulf

name: 대머들물
contents: 지형지세가 개의 형국이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name derived from the natural features looking like  a dog

name: 호근여물
contents: 범의 아가리 형태의 여 근처에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its location near the rocks having a look of the mouth of tiger

name: 농개물
contents: 고기를 잡으려 투망하던 목이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be the place to throw a cast net

name: 분드르물
contents: 마을과 멀리 분리하여 떨어진 들판이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the field is separated way long from the village

name: 괸물
engContents: it originally means a still water

name: 큰물
contents: 수량이 풍부하고 큰 샘이라는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this is a large fountain having an abundant amount of water

name: 주어미수개미동굴
contents: 다양한 어족이 모여드는 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this is located in front of a sea having different species of fish

name: 주어물
contents: 다양한 어족이 모여드는 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this is located in front of a sea having different species of fish

name: 모살-꼽지
engContents: this name suggests that it is a sandy corner

name: 엉앞물
contents: 바위그늘 앞 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain is located in the shade of rocks at the seashore.

name: 고른-참
contents: 대정현과 정의현의 경계선, 참은 5리를 나타내는 거리의 단위로서 말을 바꾸어 타던 장소
engContents: this place is a border between Daejeonghyeon and Jeongeuihyeon, where they used to change horses to ride. Cham means 5 ris as a measuring unit of distance

name: 동물
contents: 새모슬촌락의 동쪽에 있는 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain is located in the east of Saemoseul village

name: 조개물
contents: 조개하나 크기만큼 작다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its small size as a shell

name: 조선물
contents: 강수량에 상관없이 주기적으로 수량이 늘고 주는것이 간만의 차에 의해 들고나는 물과 같다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name suggests that the amount of water increases depending on the rise and fall of the tide regarless of rainfall

name: 쉬남-물
contents: 주민들이 바다에서 일을 마치고 올 때나, 다른 곳으로 일을 보러 갈 때 쉬어가며 물을 마셨던 곳
engContents: this used to be a place where villagers had a rest to get some water

name: 동남물
engContents: this name derived from the fact that the stream flows to the east

name: 칭계-왓
engContents: this name was came from the image of the field which looks like a staircase

name: 돌무깡물
contents: 샘 주변에 돌무더기가 많이 쌓여 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain name derived from the fact that there are files of rocks nearby

name: 세추맥이
contents: 부락에 큰 일이 나면 종을 쳤는데 종을 달아 매었던 언덕
engContents: this hill used to have an alarm bell to warn people of danger or emergency in the village

name: 원개물
contents: 샘의 모양이 둥그런 원형이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain name derived from the fact it has a round shape

name: 속당-모루
contents:
"옛날 조농사가 잘 된다는 지경을 말할 때 조농사 하면 당연히
 속당마루
 라 하여 불려지게 됨 "
engContents: this name came from the meaning of smooth millet cultivation

name: 들렁머리옆
contents: 낮은 언덕 밑에 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: 낮은 언덕 밑에 있어 붙여진 이름	지명	this name derived from the fact that it is located under a small hill

name: 무도못
contents: 샘이 있는 마을의 위쪽에 있다하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: the name derived from the fact that it is located above a village having a fountain

name: 뱀주리
contents:
"고려말 
 묵호의 난
 을 진압하기위하여 고려 군사들이 
 범섬
 으로 도망간 
 목호
 들을 진압하기 위해 이곳에서부터 
 범섬
 까지 뗏목을 이었다고 하여 불려진 이름"
engContents: "this name came from the historical episode Goryeo solidiers connected rafts from this place to Beom island in order to put down on rebellions such as

name: 도네기물통
contents: 밀물때면 이곳에서도 물이 솟는다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: the fountain name derived from the fact water springs from here each tide

name: 할미-개
contents:
"할미
 는 만처럼 휘어져 들어간 작은 곳을 뜻함, 그런 포구"
engContents: Halmi means a small place looking like a gulf and this is a port of such features

name: 멜든-통
contents: 멸치가 들어 와 미처 빠져나가지 못해 잡히는 곳

name: 괴기물
engContents: the place name derived from the fact eels live there

name: 송장-사라란-빌레
engContents: this name suggests in this base rock they used to burn the bodies

name: 앙당수
contents: 바다와 경계를 이루는 물이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain forms a border to the sea

name: 몰망-올리는-디
contents:
"몰망
 은 해조류의 일종, 몰망이 자주 올라 와 쌓이는 곳"
engContents: "this name was derived from the fact a pile of the seaweed called

name: 개맡물
contents: 바닷가 포구에서 솟아나는 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name suggests that the fountain is located near the port

name: 문다두리-코지
contents: 문다두리는 고동의 일종,그 것이 많이 잡히는 곶
engContents: "this name was derived from the fact this is a cape for catching

name: 진세미물
contents: 맑은 샘이 솟아나는 곳이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name suggests that the the fountain has clear water

name: 벌러진-밧
engContents: this name came from the fact that a thunderbolt struck the field divided

name: 황토산물
contents: 황토빛의 물이 난다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name suggests that the fountain has hwangto(earthy yellow)-colored water

name: 봉안이물
contents: 봉황의 눈처럼 생긴 바위 옆에 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name means  that  the fountain was located next to a rock having a look of Bongwhang birds eye

name: 걸매-목
engContents: this name suggests the entrance of Geolmae

name: 서수포
contents: 바닷물에 육지가 씻기는 포구라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name means that the port was getting swept by waves

name: 조름지
engContents: this name suggests that the end was tied up

name: 냇각물
contents: 하천의 끄트머리에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name means that the fountain was located at the end of river

name: 걸-매
engContents: this name suggests a stream whose gutter often gets chocked

name: 냇붕리
contents: 하천의 봉우리 같다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this named suggests a top of river

name: 내중-난-밧
engContents: this name  suggests  this field was reclaimed later

name: 웃수
contents: 고망물 위에 있는 소(沼)라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name refers to the swamp over Gomangmul

name: 말물
contents: 지형이 곡식을 담는 말(斗)의 모양과 같다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name originates from the natural features having a look of mal as a measuring device for grains

name: 앙강물
contents: 경계를 이루는 물이라는 암곰물이 변형된 이름
engContents: this name originates from Amgommul(water making a boundary)

name: 망냉이-왓
engContents: this name implies a field where a youngest son used to live

name: 고망물
contents: 바위틈 구멍에서 물이 솟는데서 연유한 이름
engContents: this name originates from the fountain gushing out of rock cracks

name: 덩더렁-우영
contents:
"덩더렁
 은 짚이나 대를 다루기 위한 둥그런 돌이다. 덩더렁으로 이루어진 텃밭"
engContents: Deongdeoreong is a round stone to deal with straw or bamboo and this is a field that consists of Deongdeoreongs

name: 배등개물
contents: 포구에서 출어하는 배들이 이 샘에서 물을 길어간데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name originates from fishing boats taking water from this fountain when leaving from the port to fish

name: 궷물
contents: 바닷가 근처 천연동굴(궤)에 연못처럼 물이 고여있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: it suggests that it looks like a pond in the natural cave(Goe) by the seashore

name: 넙빌레물
contents: 암반이 넓게 깔린 곳에 샘이 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: it refers to its being in a rock bed

name: 멀천통
engContents: it suggests there is a rock having a look of tong(barrel)

name: 하-논
engContents: this means a zone with lots of paddy field and also is a place name

name: 새보름코망
contents: 새 부리처럼 생겼다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: it referrs to its shape being named for beak of bird

name: 연제-골
engContents: it has the image of a swallow sitting on its eggs

name: 보말동물
engContents: it referrs to  the natural features having a look of mackerel

name: 몰-질
engContents: down this road they used to drive the cattle

name: 앵고무랑여물
contents: 바닷가 주변의 여 이름을 따 지어진 이름
engContents: it was named after a rock by the sea

name: 가막여물
engContents: this fountain name was derived from the fact there are lots of dark rocks in the seashore

name: 몰물-도
contents: 방목중인 말들이 물을 먹을 수 있게 냇물을 막아놓은 곳
engContents: the stream was dammed here to provide horses at grass with water

name: 사발통
contents: 사발모양의 여에 샘이 난다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: it referrs to the fountain springing out of a rock of bowl shape

name: 분토-왓
engContents: this field used to have horse droppings around

name: 영등물
engContents: it is named for Yeongdeunghalmang(Granny Yeondeung)

name: 제석-동산
contents: 제석은 농신을 뜻함, 마을제를 지냈던 동산
engContents: Jeseok means the agricultural god and in this hill they used to perform a religious service for the village

name: 팔통물
contents: 팔통이라는 샘의 근처에서 난다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: ît refers to the water coming out near a well called Paltong

name: 모살앙코지
contents: 모래밭에 샘이 난다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: it means a fountain in the sands

name: 종재기- 동산
engContents: this place looks like a small plate called Jongji

name: 전쟁이물
